    "problem": "Every financial document — invoices, balance sheets, reports, payroll records — was still handwritten, one copy at a time. A clerk might spend an entire day copying a single balance sheet. Simultaneously, a wave of corporate fraud and railway company collapses in the 1840s–60s was destroying investor confidence because no independent professional was verifying company accounts.",
